cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE

The paper proposes a new approach to designing processor accelerators, which involves introducing a supervisor layer to coordinate the job of the cores and allowing them to outsource part of the job to neighboring cores. This suggests a focus on parallel computing and distributed systems, which are covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.PF (Performance), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Among these, cs.AR and cs.PF are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the proposed changes in the processor architecture and operation.
